WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Well, amen. Thank you, Tim and Lydia.

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:10.000
And certainly our God is faithful. He is good. He is immutable. He never changes.

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:15.000
And because of that, and I love what they sang, I will bless His name. Amen.

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:20.000
And what a blessing and thankful for that song this morning.

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:25.000
I had no idea they were singing that song, but it's awesome how the Lord leads and directs.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:33.000
I have your Bible with you, John chapter 14. John chapter number 14 is where we'll begin this morning.

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:39.000
And someone asked me a couple of weeks ago, Pastor, are you going to finish the book of James?

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:43.000
And I said, I am. Amen. We're going to get back to the book of James.

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:48.000
And then this past week when I sent Holly the title for the message, she said,

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:53.000
you know you haven't been in James, right? And I'm like, yep, I'm aware of that. Amen.

00:00:53.000 --> 00:01:00.000
And I do plan to get back to the book of James. I've thoroughly enjoyed teaching and preaching through the book of James.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.000
This, our calendar year, of course, our theme is doers of the word.

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:08.000
But God has just laid some things on my heart the last several weeks.

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:13.000
And I felt led of the Lord to preach some messages that are outside of the book of James.

00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:18.000
And we'll get back there and we'll plan to finish the entirety of the book, studying through it.

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:22.000
And we're thankful for God's word.

00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:32.000
Our world this morning is filled with turmoil, conflict, trouble, and fear.

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:38.000
It really is. There are many today that are struggling with anxiety.

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:44.000
In fact, if you were to look up the statistics, it's alarming as to the percentage of American people

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:47.000
that are suffering with anxiety.

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:52.000
People that are going to see doctors and receiving treatment and etc.

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:57.000
with regard to this situation with anxiety. It's real.

00:01:57.000 --> 00:02:02.000
And we see all of these things around us and we are aware of the day in which we're living.

00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:11.000
And we find that God has revealed to us in his word that these last days would be marked by troubled times.

00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:16.000
And we find that there would be wicked men that would rise up.

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:24.000
And the Bible tells us that they would be evil and that they would deceive and they would be deceived.

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:29.000
And we see all sorts of things that are going on in our world around us.

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:34.000
As we think about the context of John chapter 14 this morning,

00:02:34.000 --> 00:02:40.000
we find really that these are the days that are leading to the crucifixion of the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:46.000
We find that the Lord Jesus Christ in these days leading to the cross of Calvary,

00:02:46.000 --> 00:02:50.000
that he would spend much time with his disciples.

00:02:50.000 --> 00:02:54.000
And we understand that in those moments that he would spend with his disciples,

00:02:54.000 --> 00:02:59.000
that he provided them with some valuable instruction.

00:02:59.000 --> 00:03:06.000
We find that for nearly three years, these disciples had had the opportunity to walk with the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:09.000
God in flesh.

00:03:09.000 --> 00:03:15.000
It's absolutely amazing to consider the privilege and opportunity that these men had.

00:03:15.000 --> 00:03:20.000
They were eyewitnesses of the many mighty miracles of the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:27.000
They really had front row seats, if you will, to many of his powerful sermons and his teaching.

00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:32.000
And they had those moments of not only when Jesus would teach the multitudes,

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:37.000
but even after he would teach the multitudes, they had the opportunity in a private setting

00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:42.000
to inquire further and deeper and say, what do you mean by this?

00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:49.000
And it's absolutely amazing, extraordinary, if you will, to consider the opportunity that these men had.

00:03:49.000 --> 00:03:55.000
The time had come, however, we find that John uses the terminology about the hour.

00:03:55.000 --> 00:03:58.000
You'll see that reference throughout the gospel of John.

00:03:58.000 --> 00:04:02.000
It begins in chapter two and he says, the hour's not yet come.

00:04:02.000 --> 00:04:07.000
But it reveals itself in John 17 where the Bible says that the hour has come.

00:04:07.000 --> 00:04:12.000
And we understand the hour, which is being referenced in the gospel of John,

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:16.000
is the time in which the Lord Jesus Christ would go to Calvary.

00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:19.000
He would suffer upon an old rugged cross.

00:04:19.000 --> 00:04:22.000
And they played that during the offertory this morning.

00:04:22.000 --> 00:04:27.000
And he would suffer and he would bleed and he would die and he would be buried in a borrowed tomb.

00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:31.000
But we understand that he would rise, conquering sin, death, and the grave.

00:04:31.000 --> 00:04:35.000
And he would make the payment for the sin of humanity.

00:04:35.000 --> 00:04:40.000
And we find that thereafter, about 40 days later, he would ascend up into heaven.

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:47.000
And now, even still to this very day, we find that he ever liveth to make intercession for us.

00:04:47.000 --> 00:04:52.000
We know, we have the assurance, in fact, in the beginning of this chapter I have you in John 14.

00:04:53.000 --> 00:04:59.000
That we read those wonderfully encouraging and comforting words when Jesus said,

00:04:59.000 --> 00:05:03.000
let not your heart be troubled. Amen?

00:05:03.000 --> 00:05:06.000
Let not your heart be troubled.

00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:09.000
He said, you believe in God, believe also in me.

00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:12.000
In my father's house are many mansions.

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:15.000
If it were not so, I would have told you.

00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:19.000
I go to prepare a place for you.

00:05:19.000 --> 00:05:22.000
And what a great truth that is, but then it gets better.

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:25.000
He says, and if I go and prepare a place for you,

00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:34.000
I will come again and receive you unto myself that where I am, there ye may be also.

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:37.000
That's how the 14th chapter of the book of John begins.

00:05:37.000 --> 00:05:40.000
Let not your heart be troubled.

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:41.000
Why were they troubled?

00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:47.000
Because of all the news that they had received about the things that would transpire in the days ahead

00:05:47.000 --> 00:05:50.000
with Jesus going to Calvary.

00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:56.000
We find that Jesus is providing them with this wonderful instruction, and I believe,

00:05:56.000 --> 00:06:04.000
and I understand as I read the chapters 13, 14, 15, and 16 in the gospel of John,

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:11.000
I understand how desperately the disciples needed that instruction.

00:06:11.000 --> 00:06:19.000
How just appropriate it was that Jesus would take them and give them this instruction.

00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:24.000
But we understand today that God's word has been preserved for us,

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:33.000
and God has preserved the record of these interactions of this instruction that he gave to his disciples

00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:37.000
when they were facing the difficult days that they were facing,

00:06:37.000 --> 00:06:43.000
when they were in a position where their hearts were troubled because of the circumstances,

00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:50.000
and we find that that instruction that was needful for them is needful for us as well.

00:06:50.000 --> 00:06:55.000
And we find that the Bible says in verse number 27 of John 14,

00:06:55.000 --> 00:06:58.000
I want you to notice as Jesus says,

00:06:59.000 --> 00:07:03.000
Peace I leave with you.

00:07:03.000 --> 00:07:09.000
My peace I give unto you.

00:07:09.000 --> 00:07:12.000
Not as the world giveth, give I unto you.

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:20.000
Let not your heart be troubled, neither let it be afraid.

00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:25.000
He begins the chapter, let not your heart be troubled.

00:07:25.000 --> 00:07:30.000
He says in verse 27, at the end of the verse, let not your heart be troubled,

00:07:30.000 --> 00:07:33.000
neither let it be afraid.

00:07:33.000 --> 00:07:38.000
But we find that the reason that he would tell the disciples,

00:07:38.000 --> 00:07:42.000
the reason that he would give them this instruction to not be troubled,

00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:47.000
to not be afraid, is because of this word peace.

00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:50.000
And he says, peace I leave with you.

00:07:50.000 --> 00:07:57.000
My peace I give unto you, not as the world giveth.

00:07:57.000 --> 00:08:02.000
The word peace, as you look in the 1828 Noel Webster's Dictionary,

00:08:02.000 --> 00:08:12.000
it means the tranquil state of a soul assured of its salvation through Christ.

00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:16.000
Are you 100% sure this morning that heaven is your home?

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:20.000
I'm saying blessed assurance this morning, praise God.

00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:22.000
Blessed assurance.

00:08:22.000 --> 00:08:24.000
Jesus is mine.

00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:26.000
Hallelujah.

00:08:26.000 --> 00:08:32.000
The tranquil state of a soul assured of its salvation through Christ

00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:39.000
and so fearing nothing from God and content with its earthly lot

00:08:39.000 --> 00:08:43.000
of whatsoever sort that is.

00:08:43.000 --> 00:08:46.000
That's a great definition for peace.

00:08:46.000 --> 00:08:51.000
And it's a lot different than the peace that many are seeking today.

00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:54.000
So I want to preach a message that I've simply entitled this morning,

00:08:54.000 --> 00:08:56.000
The Peace of God.

00:08:56.000 --> 00:08:57.000
The Peace of God.

00:08:57.000 --> 00:09:00.000
Number one, if you're taking notes, and I only have two points,

00:09:00.000 --> 00:09:02.000
but I have a whole lot of sub points this morning,

